0. 写在前面：「互动听力-对话总结-模板」所参考的评分标准与答题准则

0.1 模板所参考的【评分标准】

「对话总结」的评分标准，与多邻国所有的「写作题型」一模一样，其大致可以分为下面四点：

① 答案长度越长越好 —— 多邻国给出的范文长度超过了50个单词；

② 词汇的高级程度（CEFR级别）越高越好 —— 用高级词汇替代自己常用的简单词汇；

③ 语法越复杂越好 —— 尽量要有从句和多变的时态；

④ 答案要引用前面「听力对答」环节的内容 —— 尽量还原背景介绍与场景对话的内容，不能瞎说，不能跑题。

基于此评分标准，本文提供的全部难度水平的模板 ——

△ 都会帮助你引用到「听力对答」环节中，【背景介绍】与【场景对话】的关键信息，确保你的答案不会跑题；

△ 同时，对于不同难度，不同分数水平的模板而言，其【模板长度（字数）】、【高级词汇的浓度】，以及【从句的个数】，都会随着模板所对应的分值的提升而“有所增加”，以确保不同目标分数的同学，都能够有最适合自己目标的模板 —— 既不会“吃不饱”，也不会“吃太撑”。

0.2 模板所参考的【答题准则】

① 「对话总结」的答题时间只有 75 秒；

② 「对话总结」的答案内容要使用【第一人称】；

③ 答案中要使用与【过去】有关的时态；

④ 答案开头要直截了当，开门见山。

基于此答题准则，本文提供的模板 ——

△ 在不太重要的模板句前都标注了“答题时间不够可以省略”的字样。

（当然了，如果你省略了这些句子，肯定会使得答案长度变短，高级词汇和语法的数量降低，进而拉低分数。因此，打字时的手速也是很重要的，需要你多多练习）；

△ 全部使用了【第一人称 —— “ I ”】；

△ 全部使用了【一般过去时态】或者其他【其他与“过去”相关的时态】；

△ 全部使用了【 I was a/an <我的身份> 】这样的开头句。

1. 模板的【使用方法】

1.1 模板的难度分级

本文提供的所有模板被划分为了三个难度分级，即

简单模板 —— 对应目标总分「 90~110分 」；

中等模板 —— 对应目标总分「 115~130分 」；

复杂模板 —— 对应目标总分「 135+分 」。

1.2 模板“不重样”

1.2.1 自主选搭模板

为了避免【查重】问题，也就是“看过本攻略的同学在考试中使用了一模一样的模板，进而被AI和人工组建的审核团队察觉，最终不予认证（不予出分，没有成绩）”的这种情况，本文中全部模板的【每一句话】（除去模板第一句，其都是 “I was a/an <我的身份>”这样的句式），我都通过替换「同义词」或者「同义表达」的方式，给予它了【三种变化】。

也就是说，模板的【每一句话】，你都可以【从三个选项中选一个】来构成。

如此一来，每一个模板都能够通过“在每句话的三个选项中选一个”的方式，衍生出少则【 81种 】（简单模板），多则【 729种 】（复杂模板）的细微差别。

甚至，你还可以将三个模板每个句子中的三个选项，全部拿来作为你的【模板素材库】，进而从中选搭拼接出你自己的【独一无二的个性化模板】。

而这样制作模板的目的，就是希望能够显著降低“你所选搭出的模板和很多考生所使用的模板一模一样”的概率，最终提升你的考试被认证（顺利出分）的机会。

因此，在记忆和使用模板之前，请你在模板每句话对应的【三个选项】中 —— 自由选择一个你中意的选项，并最终选搭出你的个性化【选搭模板】。

1.2.2 模板需要引用的「听力对答」环节的关键信息

每个模板都需要你自行引用「听力对答」环节中的下述关键信息：

[1] 我的身份

[2] 对方的身份

[3] 我遇到了什么麻烦 / 我想要咨询什么问题或者寻求什么帮助

[4] 对方给我的建议或者解决方案


其中，前三个关键信息来源于【背景介绍】，第四个关键信息来源于【场景对话】（在【场景对话】中也可能会有对第三个关键信息的补充）。

因此，请大家完成「听力对答」环节时尽量精确地记忆这四个关键信息，以便在“对话总结”环节补全模板。

2. 简单模板：对应目标总分「90~110分」

2.1 模板直给


2.2 单词释义

  • come across v. 偶遇；无意中发现
  • encounter /ɪnˈkaʊntər/ v. 偶遇；遭遇
  • grateful /ˈɡreɪtf(ə)l/ adj. 感谢的

2.3 简单模板-使用案例

我在模板每个句子的三个选项中，都选择 [A]选项 形成了下方的【选搭模板】：

I was a/an 「我的身份」 and I came across a problem with 「我遇到了什么麻烦 / 我想要咨询什么问题或者寻求什么帮助」. I asked 「对方的身份」 for help, and he/she suggested that I should 「对方给我的建议或者解决方案」. I was grateful for his/her help and advice.

将这段模板放入「CEFR检查器网站」自测后（本网站的使用方法，我会在随后的攻略中补上），可以得知这段模板的【词汇语法综合CEFR级别】为 —— 【 B1.7 】，对应雅思 5 分，对应多邻国总分 95 分左右。

换句话说，就算不引用背景介绍和场景对话的关键信息，仅仅就模板本身的内容而言，简单模板就已经达到了多邻国 95 分左右的水平。

接下来看一个使用案例 —— 我们来用上面这个模板对下面的例题进行【对话总结】。

（例题中会被模板引用到的关键信息，我都以「下划线」的形式在例题中进行了标注）

【使用案例1】

背景介绍

You are a student in the Biology department and you want to know how you can get involved in research opportunities as an undergraduate. You talk to your advisor, who has been doing research for many years, and they tell you about the different ways you can get involved in research projects.

场景对话

Student: Hi, Professor. I wanted to talk to you about getting involved in research opportunities as an undergraduate student.

Professor: Sure, what would you like to know?

Student: Well, I'm not really sure where to start. Can you tell me a bit about your own experience with research and how you got started?

Professor: I started out as an undergraduate student just like you. I got involved in a project that was studying the effects of different types of pollution on marine life. From there, I went on to get my doctorate in Biology and now I run my own research lab.

Student: Wow, that's really impressive. How did you get involved in the project as an undergraduate?

Professor: A friend of mine who was working on the project recruited me. I didn't have any previous experience with research but I was interested in the topic so I decided to give it a try. After working on that project, I realized that I really loved research and wanted to pursue it further as a career.

Student: That's really helpful, thank you! So it sounds like networking is important for getting involved in research projects?

Professor: Yes, definitely. Getting your name out there and talking to people who are already involved in the field is a great way to find out about opportunities. There are also some funding organizations that support undergraduate research projects so that's something else you can look into.

Student: Great, thank you for all the advice!


下面就是用【选搭模板】对其进行的总结：

I was a student in the Biology department and I came across a problem with getting involved in research opportunities as an undergraduate. I asked my advisor for help, and he suggested that I should network with people who are already involved in the field and look into some funding organizations that support undergraduate research projects. I was grateful for his help and advice.

而将上面这段使用了【简单模板】得出的对话总结，放入「CEFR检查器网站」自测后得出的结果是 —— 这段话的「词汇语法综合CEFR级别」为【 B 2.4 】，其对应雅思 6 分，对应多邻国 110 分左右！

不过有一说一，【简单模板】本身并不会对应这么高的CEFR级别与多邻国分数，只是模板能够帮助你快速地引用前面的背景介绍和场景对话环节的关键信息，进而更简单直接地输出「对话总结」的内容。而「模板本身+引用的关键信息」则对应了多邻国 110 分这个较高的分数段。

  • hurdle /ˈhɜrdl/ n. 障碍；跳栏
  • run up against v. 遭遇；碰到（困难）
  • snag /snæɡ/ n. 障碍；问题
  • bump into v. 撞上；偶然遇见
  • render /ˈrɛndər/ v.提供
  • solicite /səˈlɪsɪt/ v. 恳求；征求
  • inquire /ɪnˈkwaɪər/ v. 询问
  • circumstance /ˈsɜrkəmstæns/ n. 情况；境遇
  • counsel /ˈkaʊnsəl/ v. 劝告
  • cherish /ˈtʃɛrɪʃ/ v. 珍爱；珍视

  • convey /kənˈveɪ/ v. 传达
  • sincere /sɪnˈsɪr/ adj. 真诚的
  • appreciation /əpriʃiˈeɪʃən/ n.感激
  • supportive /səˈpɔrtɪv/ adj. 支持的
  • comforting /ˈkʌmfərtɪŋ/ adj.令人欣慰的
  • productive /prəˈdʌktɪv/ adj. 富有成效的

3.3 中等模板-使用案例

这次，我将中等模板中每一个句子的 [B]选项 抽取出来，形成如下的【选搭模板】：

I was a/an 「我的身份」, and I ran up against a snag with 「我遇到了什么麻烦 / 我想要咨询什么问题或者寻求什么帮助」. I solicited support from 「对方的身份」, and I described the issue and the challenges that I encountered. Following that, he/she directed me that I should 「对方给我的建议或者解决方案」. I was immensely thankful for his/her assistance and guidance. The chat was beneficial and comforting.


测一下这个模板的【词汇语法综合CEFR级别】，得到的结果是 —— 【 B 2.8 】，这个级别对应了雅思 6.5 分，多邻国的 120-125 分。

接下来看一个案例 —— 我们用这个选搭模板，来对下面的例题进行总结。


【使用案例2】

背景介绍：

You are a student in a Creative Writing class. You arrived to class late one day and missed an important announcement from the professor regarding an upcoming assignment.

场景对话：

Student: Professor, I'm sorry I was late to class today. Did you say something about the assignment due next week?

Professor: I did. The assignment will be a bit different from what we've done in the past. Instead of writing a short story, I want you to write a play.

Student: A play?

Professor: Yes, a short one-act play. It can be anything you want, but it should be around 10 pages long.

Student: Okay, that sounds doable. But why a play?

Professor: We've been doing a lot of work on prose in this class and I thought it would be good to switch things up and try something new. Besides, plays are a lot of fun to write!

Student: Yeah, I guess so. Do you have any suggestions for what kind of play I should write?

Professor: Nope. It can be anything you want. You could even adapt one of your old short stories into a play if you wanted to.

Student: Alright then, I'll think about it and figure out what might be best. Thanks Professor!

以下为使用了选搭模板后的对话总结内容：

I was a student in a Creative Writing class, and I ran up against a snag with the assignment due next week. I solicited support from the professor, and I described the issue and the challenges that I encountered. Following that, she directed me that I should write a short one-act play which could be in any form instead of a short story I had done much in the class. I was immensely thankful for her assistance and guidance. The chat was beneficial and comforting.


有了背景介绍与场景对话中的关键信息的填充，这段基于选搭模板形成的对话总结内容，其能够对应多邻国 125-130 这个分数段。

4.3 复杂模板 – 使用案例

在本案例中，我们先用复杂模板中每句话的 [C]选项，形成如下的选搭模板：

I was a/an 「我的身份」, and I stumbled upon a difficulty with 「我需要咨询的问题或者想要寻求的帮助」. I solicited 「对方的身份」 who was pretty supportive for assistance. And I clarified the situation and the hindrances that I should surmount. Afterwards, he/she endowed me with some recommendations and solutions, which were that 「对方给我的建议或者解决方案」. I articulated my thankfulness for his/her partnership and direction. The dialogue was enlightening and inspiring.


将这个选搭模板放入「CEFR检查器」，得到其【词汇语法综合CEFR级别】为 —— 【 C1.6 】，这是一个接近最高级别C2的模板，它对应了雅思 8 分，多邻国 150 分！

所以，对于目标分数在 135 分以上的同学，完全可以使用【复杂模板】来回答对话总结题，让自己的分数锦上添花。

接下来，我们用这个模板来对下面的例题进行总结。


【使用案例3】

背景介绍

You are a student in a Political Science class and you are in the process of writing a paper on environmental policy making. You have found some sources, but you need help finding additional sources to support your argument. You go to talk to your professor during their review session to get some help.

场景对话

Professor: Hi there. What can I do for you?

Student: Hi, Professor. I'm working on my paper on environmental policy making and I was hoping to get some help finding sources.

Professor: Sure, what kind of sources are you looking for?

Student: I need some sources that talk about how countries are working together to propose joint solutions to environmental problems we're facing.

Professor: Okay, let me see... Have you tried looking at news articles? There have been a lot of recent events that have brought environmental policy to the forefront.

Student: Yeah, I've read a few articles but I'm looking for something more in-depth.

Professor: Have you checked out any academic journals? There's been some good research done on the topic in the past few years.

Student: No, I didn't know where to start looking. Do you have any specific suggestions?

Professor: Let me look and see what I can find... Here's a couple of journals that often report on the topic that might be helpful. You could also look for the book, "Environmental Policy Design in the 21st Century", in the library.

Student: Thank you so much, Professor! I'll be sure to read through these.

以下为使用选搭模板后的总结内容：

I was a student in a Political Science class, and I stumbled upon a difficulty with finding additional sources to support my argument on environmental policy making. I solicited my professor who was pretty supportive for assistance. And I clarified the situation and the hindrances that I should surmount. Afterwards, she endowed me with some recommendations and solutions, which were that I should look at news articles, academic journals, and a book on the topic. I articulated my thankfulness for her partnership and direction. The dialogue was enlightening and inspiring.


有了关键信息的填充，上述答案差不多应该就是对话总结题的天花板了。

5. 模板打字练习

「对话总结」环节的整体答题时间只有 75 秒，这对于既要「完整输入模板」，同时还要「精确引用对话关键信息」来说，时间是极其紧张的。

而想要解决这一问题，提高打字输入模板的【速度与手感】就显得尤其重要了。

这也是为什么我要在这里强调 ——

对于模板的掌握，绝对不能仅仅止步于“把模板记住”，而是要通过【大量的打字练习】，巩固加深对于模板的记忆，同时提升打字输入模板的速度。

打字练习的方法很简单：

在你选定并记住了自己的「选搭模板」后，只需要打开Word，然后在其中打字输入，默写这个模板即可。

建议每天（包括考试当天）至少安排【3个10分钟】来进行这样的「模板打字练习」，以形成模板打字输入的肌肉记忆，缩短模板输入时间，以节约出更多的时间用来将题目中的「关键信息」填充进模板。

6. 选定【两套】选搭模板

由于在每次的真实考试中，都会有【两道】互动听力题目。

因此建议你选定并练熟【两个】选搭模板，来应对这两道互动听力中的对话总结题。

如果你只用了一个选搭模板来回答这两个对话总结题，我担心审核团队在看到了两道对话总结题中出现的一模一样的模板时，会有概率判定你为：“提前准备好了答案”，而不认证你的这次考试（不出分）。
